He had his wife with him.

103
00:06:23,684 --> 00:06:25,151
'You all gonna want
to stay in here tonight?'

104
00:06:25,251 --> 00:06:27,754
'I can get some clean sheets
and towels from the‐‐'

105
00:06:27,854 --> 00:06:31,091
No, thank you. But, uh, if you
have a couple of extra rooms..

106
00:06:31,191 --> 00:06:32,526
‐ Adjoining?
‐ Fine.

107
00:06:32,626 --> 00:06:33,694
Mm‐hmm.

108
00:06:34,628 --> 00:06:36,630
Such a nice couple.

109
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:38,965
‐ Terrible what happened.
‐ Yeah.

110
00:06:41,001 --> 00:06:43,537
‐ Wife?
‐ I doubt it.

111
00:06:43,637 --> 00:06:45,405
Who's that?

112
00:06:45,506 --> 00:06:47,508
I have no idea.

113
00:06:47,608 --> 00:06:50,443
‐ Is that you?
‐ Where?

114
00:06:50,544 --> 00:06:52,412
Yeah. That's, uh,
that's high school.

115
00:06:52,513 --> 00:06:54,515
Look at that hair.
Played varsity?

116
00:06:54,615 --> 00:06:55,949
Yeah, we went
to state that year.

117
00:06:56,049 --> 00:06:59,119
Yeah. I played JV.
I was...wasn't very good.

118
00:07:01,622 --> 00:07:02,989
Oh, man.

119
00:07:04,658 --> 00:07:06,126
Your mom?

120
00:07:06,993 --> 00:07:08,695
Yeah.

121
00:07:12,866 --> 00:07:14,535
For a guy that didn't care..

122
00:07:14,635 --> 00:07:16,837
