134
00:07:55,909 --> 00:07:57,978
...or a cocktail waitress
or something.

135
00:07:58,078 --> 00:07:59,212
Is there any money in here?

136
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:03,049
No, just a couple
of pawn tickets.

137
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:05,752
Well, there it is.
There's my inheritance.

138
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:07,854
Some women's clothes..

139
00:08:07,954 --> 00:08:09,990
'...a couple of half‐empty
liquor bottles..'

140
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:11,992
...and, uh, two pawn tickets.

141
00:08:12,092 --> 00:08:14,060
Sounds like my dad.

142
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,128
'Well, here you are.'

143
00:08:16,229 --> 00:08:18,031
Whoo!

144
00:08:18,131 --> 00:08:19,733
Thirteen.

145
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,569
Fourteen. Oh, honey!

146
00:08:22,669 --> 00:08:25,906
Down on the corner,
away from the highway noise.

147
00:08:26,006 --> 00:08:29,743
Oh, I forgot
to tell you earlier.

148
00:08:29,843 --> 00:08:32,145
Your daddy's car
is parked around back.

149
00:08:32,245 --> 00:08:33,914
Oh, he...he didn't wreck it?

150
00:08:34,014 --> 00:08:35,782
No, it must have been her car.

151
00:08:35,882 --> 00:08:37,784
'His car's still here.'

152
00:08:44,324 --> 00:08:47,961
Son of a bitch...he kept it.

153
00:08:48,061 --> 00:08:50,664
He was always out here,
polishing it.

154
00:08:50,764 --> 00:08:53,634
Said he'd had it
for years.

155
00:08:53,734 --> 00:08:56,269
Since the '70s.

156
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:57,270
'It's a beauty!'

157
00:09:01,074 --> 00:09:02,876
Hey, maybe the keys are
with your dad's stuff.

158
00:09:02,976 --> 00:09:05,311
That envelope's still
in the rental car.

159
00:09:05,411 --> 00:09:07,681
Pull the garage door
shut and lock it, huh..

160
00:09:07,781 --> 00:09:09,315
...when you're finished,
alright?

161
00:09:09,415 --> 00:09:10,851
Yeah.

162
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:27,193
I learned to drive
in this car.

163
00:10:27,293 --> 00:10:28,194
Yeah?

164
00:10:30,897 --> 00:10:33,634
Yeah, my dad. We wouldn't see
him for months.

165
00:10:33,734 --> 00:10:35,636
Then he'd just
show up, and he'd just..

166
00:10:35,736 --> 00:10:37,070
He'd bring my mom a present.

167
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:39,906
He'd bring me a‐a signed
football from, uh..

168
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:43,076
...Joe Namath,
Bob Griese or somebody.

169
00:10:43,176 --> 00:10:45,812
And, uh, then he'd
gather me up

170
00:10:45,912 --> 00:10:47,648
and he'd tell my mom
we were going to a ball game

171
00:10:47,748 --> 00:10:48,915
which she knew was a lie

172
00:10:49,015 --> 00:10:50,116
and then, we would
just hit the road.

173
00:10:50,216 --> 00:10:54,087
We'd...we'd
disappear for days.

174
00:10:54,187 --> 00:10:56,289
We'd be driving to Vegas.

175
00:10:56,389 --> 00:10:58,191
Sometimes, we'd drive
to Atlantic City.

176
00:10:58,291 --> 00:11:00,393
It was..

177
00:11:02,262 --> 00:11:04,097
It was back, uh,
it was before my mom remarried

178
00:11:04,197 --> 00:11:07,033
so we were still living in
Kentucky at the time, so..

179
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:10,737
...I was maybe
13, 12, I think, maybe.

180
00:11:12,272 --> 00:11:15,709
So, we'd be in...
Oklahoma or Indiana

181
00:11:15,809 --> 00:11:17,177
middle of the night.

182
00:11:17,277 --> 00:11:19,846
My dad would wake me up
and say, "Okay, you're driving."

183
00:11:21,782 --> 00:11:24,918
So we'd get off
on some side road..

184
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:26,953
...and I'd slide in
behind the wheel.

185
00:11:29,455 --> 00:11:30,957
Just floor it.

186
00:11:31,057 --> 00:11:34,127
Just feel those..

187
00:11:34,227 --> 00:11:36,029
...426 horses.

188
00:11:38,799 --> 00:11:41,067
It just felt like..

189
00:11:41,167 --> 00:11:42,803
...I was flying.

190
00:11:44,505 --> 00:11:46,472
Sounds pretty great.

191
00:11:49,075 --> 00:11:52,412
He had his moments.

192
00:11:56,149 --> 00:11:59,385
‐ Gas?
‐ We got a quarter of a tank.

193
00:11:59,485 --> 00:12:01,021
'Look.'

194
00:12:01,121 --> 00:12:02,355
Oh!

195
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:06,292
'Hang on.'

196
00:12:08,328 --> 00:12:09,963
Now what?

197
00:12:10,063 --> 00:12:12,866
My dad used to keep
a gas can in the trunk.

198
00:12:16,369 --> 00:12:17,838
Wow.

199
00:12:19,305 --> 00:12:20,974
You usually don't see
that much baby stuff

200
00:12:21,074 --> 00:12:22,475
all in one place.

201
00:12:29,149 --> 00:12:30,283
No gas.

202
